  "prompt": "What hotel in Darjeeling Hill-station would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "When traveling to Darjeeling, or any other destination in India, unmarried couples often seek accommodations that respect their privacy and provide a hassle-free stay. Here are some tips and recommendations for finding a hotel in Darjeeling that is welcoming to unmarried couples:\n\n1. **OYO Rooms**: Many OYO hotels are known for their couple-friendly policies. When booking, look for listings that specify \"Couple Friendly\" or use the OYO app to apply the \"Relationship Mode\" filter.\n\n2. **FabHotels**: Similar to OYO, FabHotels also offers numerous couple-friendly options. Use their website or app to filter and find suitable accommodations.\n\n3. **Airbnb**: Opting for a private Airbnb can be a good way to ensure privacy and avoid any issues with hotel policies. Make sure to communicate with the host beforehand and confirm their stance on unmarried couples.\n\n4. **Check Reviews**: Before booking, read reviews on platforms like TripAdvisor, Google, or Booking.com to ensure other couples have had positive experiences at the hotel.\n\n5. **Contact the Hotel Directly**: If you're unsure, call the hotel directly to inquire about their policies regarding unmarried couples. It's better to clarify beforehand to avoid any inconvenience.\n\n6. **Look for Reputable Chains**: Hotel chains often have standardized policies and are more likely to respect guests' privacy. Examples include Sterling, Club Mahindra, and other established brands in Darjeeling.\n\n7. **Documents**: Make sure both guests have valid ID proof, as this is generally required during check-in regardless of your relationship status.\n\nRemember, the social environment and attitudes can vary, so seeking out accommodations known for their modern approach and privacy can make your stay in Darjeeling more enjoyable.",
